  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary aim of this study was to determine the Harris hip score as an evaluation of hip
      function, in mentally competent elderly patients (&gt;65 years old) treated with either THR or
      IF, after contracting a displaced femoral neck fracture. The secondary aim was to compare the
      rate of reoperations and complications between the two groups.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
