    <measure>Harris hip score</measure>
    <time_frame>17 years</time_frame>
    <description>HHS index score of 0 indicates the worst possible function of the hip and a value of 100 indicates full function.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>Reoperations and complications</measure>
    <time_frame>17 years</time_frame>
    <description>IF group: nonunion, osteonecrosis, deep infection or fracture in the vicinity of the screws. Protruding screws or extraction of the screws when the fracture was healed was not defined as a complication.
THR group: radiographic signs of loosening of the femoral- or acetabular component, dislocation, periprosthetic fracture or deep infection</description>
